<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='411000' id='t-411000'>And then the third part is, What are the potential problems,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='415000' id='t-415000'>or the dark side of blogs as we know them?</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 7:10
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='419000' id='t-419000'>OK, the first question:</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='421000' id='t-421000'>What do they tell us about why people do things?</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='423000' id='t-423000'>One of the fascinating things about the blogosphere specifically,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='426000' id='t-426000'>and, of course, the Internet more generally --</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='429000' id='t-429000'>and it's going to seem like a very obvious point,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='431000' id='t-431000'>but I think it is an important one to think about --</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='433000' id='t-433000'>is that the people who are generating these enormous reams of content</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='437000' id='t-437000'>every day, who are spending enormous amounts of time organizing,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='442000' id='t-442000'>linking, commenting on the substance of the Internet,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='445000' id='t-445000'>are doing so primarily for free.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='448000' id='t-448000'>They are not getting paid for it in any way other than in the attention and,</span>
