<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='562000' id='t-562000'>The second question is, What does the blogosphere actually do for us,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='567000' id='t-567000'>in terms of accessing collective intelligence?</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='570000' id='t-570000'>You know, as Chris mentioned, I wrote a book called &quot;The Wisdom of Crowds.&quot;</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='573000' id='t-573000'>And the premise of &quot;The Wisdom of Crowds&quot; is that,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='576000' id='t-576000'>under the right conditions, groups can be remarkably intelligent.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='580000' id='t-580000'>And they can actually often be smarter</span>
