<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='835000' id='t-835000'>or the paradox of collective intelligence,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='837000' id='t-837000'>that what it requires is actually a form of independent thinking.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='842000' id='t-842000'>And networks make it harder for people to do that,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='846000' id='t-846000'>because they drive attention to the things that the network values.</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
14:21
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='850000' id='t-850000'>So, one of the phenomena that's very clear in the blogosphere</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='854000' id='t-854000'>is that once a meme, once an idea gets going,</span>
