<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='888000' id='t-888000'>The metaphor that I like to use is the metaphor of the circular mill.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='892000' id='t-892000'>A lot of people talk about ants.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='894000' id='t-894000'>You know, this is a conference inspired by nature.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='896000' id='t-896000'>When we talk about bottom-up, decentralized phenomena,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='899000' id='t-899000'>the ant colony is the classic metaphor, because,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='903000' id='t-903000'>no individual ant knows what it's doing,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='905000' id='t-905000'>but collectively ants are able to reach incredibly intelligent decisions.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='910793' id='t-910793'>They're able to reach food
as efficiently as possible,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='913874' id='t-913874'>they're able to guide their traffic
with remarkable speed.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='918000' id='t-918000'>So, the ant colony is a great model:</span>
